@node getenv
@chapter Accessing system environment variables


The library @library{getenv} exports a simple interface to access system
environment variables.  This library exists with the purpose of
providing a lightweight interface for the expansion of macros.


@defun getenv @var{varname}
Return a string representing the value of the environment variable
@var{varname}; the string can be empty.  If the variable is not set
return false.
@end defun

